      <hedline>
        <hl1>BRITISH WATER DEAL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Suzanne Kapner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Kapner, Suzanne</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Anglian Water, British water utility, is buying Morrison PLC, Scottish construction company, for 262.5 million pounds, or about $177 million; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In an effort to gain the scale that will allow it to bid for larger projects, Anglian Water, a British water utility, said it was buying Morrison P.L.C., a Scottish construction company, for $:262.5 million, or about $177 million. The cash deal values Morrison at 385 pence a share. The combined company is expected to focus on expanding its reach within the electricity, gas, transport and telecommunications sectors.</p>
        <p>Suzanne Kapner (NYT)</p>
      </block>
